# Skill: Route + Page Endpoint Wiring

## Goal
Add a new page route flow while preserving file boundaries.

## Required Split
- Route file: `src/routes/<name>.tsx`
- Page component: `src/features/<feature>/pages/<Name>Page.tsx`
- Service call: `src/services/<domain>/index.ts`
- Validation: `src/features/<feature>/validation/*.ts`

## Route File Rules
- Only route declaration, lazy page import, suspense fallback, optional guard.
- No direct API calls.
- No business validation logic.

## Page Rules
- Use feature hooks/state/validation.
- Delegate network calls to services.
- Use feature-specific components from `src/components/<feature>` and shared primitives from `src/components/ui`.

## Checklist
- [ ] Route is thin and lazy-loaded
- [ ] Business logic in feature page/hook
- [ ] API call in service layer
- [ ] Validation co-located in feature validation folder
